rprises itself."}, {"version": "diamond", "text": "It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain."}, {"version": "heartgold", "text": "You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it\u2019s scared, both ears are rolled up."}, {"version": "legends-arceus", "text": "My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pok\u00e9mon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears."}, {"version": "omega-ruby", "text": "Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder."}, {"version": "pearl", "text": "When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur."}, {"version": "platinum", "text": "Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder."}, {"version": "shield", "text": "Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training."}, {"version": "soulsilver", "text": "You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it\u2019s scared, both ears are rolled up."}, {"version": "sword", "text": "If both of Buneary\u2019s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It\u2019s a sure sign the Pok\u00e9mon is in need of care."}, {"version": "ultra-moon", "text": "The reason it keeps one ear rolled up is so it can launch a swift counterattack if it\u2019s attacked by an enemy."}, {"version": "ultra-sun", "text": "Its arms and legs are weak, but when it rolls its ears up tight and then unleashes them with its full force, it can smash boulders to dust."}, {"version": "white", "text": "Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder."}, {"version": "white-2", "text": "By extending its rolled-up ears and striking the ground, it can bound so high it surprises itself."}, {"version": "x", "text": "Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder."}, {"version": "y", "text": "When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur."}], "entryGameVersions": ["alpha-sapphire", "black", "black-2", "diamond", "heartgold", "legends-arceus", "omega-ruby", "pearl", "platinum", "shield", "soulsilver", "sword", "ultra-moon", "ultra-sun", "white", "white-2", "x", "y"], "moveGameGroups": ["black-2-white-2", "black-white", "brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl", "diamond-pearl", "heartgold-soulsilver", "legends-arceus", "omega-ruby-alpha-sapphire", "platinum", "sun-moon", "sword-shield", "ultra-sun-ultra-moon", "x-y"], "evolutionRows": [{"stage": 1, "name": "buneary"}, {"stage": 2, "name": "lopunny"}]}